      "answer": "DualCast solved audio-video synchronization issues by implementing a single FFmpeg mux pass combining video and audio into one WebM container, and setting the client-side Media Source Extensions (MSE) to `sequence` mode, which ignores timestamps and plays chunks in order [DualCast.md #7]. This ensures frame-perfect sync at muxing time, not client-side [DualCast.md #7].",
